<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1887-01-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1887-01-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="331" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d331">
                        <head>No. 331.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">L. S.
                                    Sackville West</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-01-28"><hi rend="italic">January</hi> 28,
                                1887</date>. (Received January 29.)</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of yesterday’s date, and to inform you that I have
                            submitted the case of the American schooner <hi rend="italic">Sarah H.
                                Prior</hi> to Her Majesty’s Government for investigation, as
                            requested by you.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">L. S. Sackville
                            West.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>